definitions.definition: A small , showy ornament , especially a piece of jewellery .
examples: That little trinket around her neck must have cost a bundle.

definitions.definition: ( figurative ) A thing of little value ; a toy , a trifle .
examples: It’s only a little trinket , but it reminds her of him.

subdefinitions.definition: A small item of food ; a small dainty .
( chiefly in the plural ) A small item forming part of a set of equipment ; an accessory , an accoutrement .
( figurative , religion , derogatory ) An item used in a religious rite (also, a religious rite, belief , etc.) regarded as superfluous or trivial.

main_definition: A small , showy ornament , especially a piece of jewellery .
secondary_definitions: ( figurative ) A thing of little value ; a toy , a trifle .

definitions.definition: ( Ireland , Northern Ireland , Scotland ) A narrow or small watercourse .

main_definition: ( Ireland , Northern Ireland , Scotland ) A narrow or small watercourse .

definitions.definition: ( UK , dialectal , chiefly Cheshire , Lancashire , obsolete ) A small vessel for drinking from; a cup , a mug , a porringer .

main_definition: ( UK , dialectal , chiefly Cheshire , Lancashire , obsolete ) A small vessel for drinking from; a cup , a mug , a porringer .

definitions.definition: A small sail , specifically, a three-cornered sail formerly carried on a ship 's foremast , probably on a lateen yard .

main_definition: ( nautical , obsolete ) A small sail , specifically, a three-cornered sail formerly carried on a ship 's foremast , probably on a lateen yard .
